HEADWORD: Ribbonwood
<hw>Rib"bon*wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A malvaceous tree (<spn>Hoheria populnea</spn>) of New Zealand, the
bark of which is used for cordage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

